Graphing Wars

Author: Christopher Steward
Source: https://github.com/cstew2/game_prototype
Redistribution: Can publish on OWL.

features:
-setting up SDL
-drawing graphical primatives
-player movement
-polygonal objects that interact with shots
-basic firing with a normal shot
-collision detection for shots and player

Libraries required:
SDL2 (https://www.libsdl.org/download-2.0.php)
SDL2_ttf (https://www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_ttf/)

Tested on:
Gentoo 2.6 (17.1 profile)
Kernel: 5.5.4
gcc: 9.2.0-r2
SDL2: 2.0.10
SDL2-ttf: 2.0.14

Build with:
make

or to build with statically linked SDL
BUILD=release make

Run with:
make run
or
navigate to correct build directory and run there

Play with:
w - up
a - left
s - down
d - right
space - fire
mouse - to aim

References:
https://lazyfoo.net/tutorials/SDL/index.php
https://wiki.libsdl.org/
https://www.libsdl.org/projects/SDL_ttf/docs/index.html
